  "text": "where the vector is the Euclidean norm from the skeleton markers positions, and is the th band-pass filter operator. The first software implementation of the PQoM was made in MATLAB and can be downloaded as an extension for the MoCap Toolbox 6 [CITATION_1] . The same approach was adopted to estimate the PQoM from data from other sensors. However, a specific vector of coeffcients must be defined regarding each sensor type, and an appropriate norm for the vector must be chosen. For instance, we used a similar approach as in Equation 2 , in which our PQoM implementation replaced with the weighted sum of the norm of the orientation quaternion (∥ ∥) with the average acceleration over the three axes.",
